name,

Before you start writing a huge long article again, slow down.

The key to the SCP Foundation is terseness: we have our roots in creepypasta, so we try to give as little info as possible. The key to all fear is fear of the unknown, so to encourage fear, leave stuff unknown.

I second Kondraki's suggestion that you not write up a huge long article on a side organization on this page. If you want, put it under groups of interest, or perhaps as an investigation report.

Finally: you have failed to grasp what the SCP report is, based on your first response: its some independent investigator writing his report and giving it to the head of security. NO. The SCP report IS the head of security telling his underlings what to do to keep the item contained and safe. An investigator's report is just that, a report, and things with that tone belong on a different page.





